<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,963,1422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,678,963,989]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Description derived from earlier literature.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[688,763,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Facies</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[781,870,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–50" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[232,1322,222,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,178,1758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40–50. Aethina (Aethina) argus Grouvelle, 1890: 40, Dorsal facies, line drawing (adapted from Grouvelle, 1890); 41, Tegmen, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 42, Median lobe, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 43. A. (A.) cyaneipennis Grouvelle, 1903: Dorsal facies (line drawing adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 44–50. A. (A.) inconspicua Nakane, 1967 (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986): 44, Tegmen of specimen from Punjab; 45, 47, Median lobe and 48, Tegmen of specimen from S. China; 46, Median lobe of specimen from Punjab; 49, Dorsal facies of specimen from Fuji; 50, Dorsal facies of specimen from Punjab." pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
): Body colour entirely testaceous-ferrugineous, a little darkened with ten black punctate spots; four on the pronotum: the first in the middle of anterior margin, the second above the scutellar shield near posterior margin, and two postero-laterally placed; five on the elytra: one sutural, and two on each sides of elytron; one in the middle of last abdominal segment. Body rather broad, oval, subconvex, densely punctate. Cuticle covered with decumbent pubescence, more distinct than base of elytra. Antennae testaceous. 
<emphasis box="[393,507,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Prothorax</emphasis>
transverse, slightly narrowed anterad, anterior margin deeply emarginate, posterior corners of pronotum somewhat projecting posterad. 
<emphasis box="[732,907,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Scutellar shield</emphasis>
transverse, punctate. 
<emphasis box="[1148,1218,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Elytra</emphasis>
with truncate apex, exposing only the last abdominal segment. 
<emphasis box="[636,742,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Abdomen</emphasis>
and metaventrite finely punctate, a little near sides. 
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,301,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–50" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[232,1322,222,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,178,1758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40–50. Aethina (Aethina) argus Grouvelle, 1890: 40, Dorsal facies, line drawing (adapted from Grouvelle, 1890); 41, Tegmen, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 42, Median lobe, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 43. A. (A.) cyaneipennis Grouvelle, 1903: Dorsal facies (line drawing adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 44–50. A. (A.) inconspicua Nakane, 1967 (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986): 44, Tegmen of specimen from Punjab; 45, 47, Median lobe and 48, Tegmen of specimen from S. China; 46, Median lobe of specimen from Punjab; 49, Dorsal facies of specimen from Fuji; 50, Dorsal facies of specimen from Punjab." pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Figs. 41, 42</figureCitation>
): Tegmen elongate, tongue-shaped, subparallel sides with rounded apex; row of setae present in the apical third at the sides. Median lobe bud shaped, slightly longer than broad with rounded apex.
</paragraph>
